  "prompt": "I know I can do best but still I can't do Nothing?",
  "response": "It's understandable to feel that way at times, but remember that everyone faces challenges and moments of doubt. Here are a few steps to help you move forward:\n\n1. **Self-Reflection:** Take some time to understand why you feel this way. Are there specific obstacles in your path? Identifying the root cause can help you address it more effectively.\n\n2. **Set Small Goals:** Break your tasks into small, manageable steps. Completing these can give you a sense of accomplishment and build momentum.\n\n3. **Seek Support:** Talk to friends, family, or a mentor about your feelings. Sometimes an outside perspective can provide valuable insight and encouragement.\n\n4. **Positive Mindset:** Try to reframe your thoughts. Focus on your strengths and past successes to remind yourself of your capabilities.\n\n5. **Take Action:** Even small actions can help you build confidence and a sense of progress. Start with something simple and gradually work your way up.\n\nRemember, it's normal to have moments of doubt, but with perseverance and support, you can overcome them.",
